commitResults.messageTitle: Add delete task and delete module commands
commitResults.messageBody:
Add delete task command feature which supports the deletion
of tasks from the address book. With this feature, unwanted
tasks can be removed easily.

Add delete module command feature which supports the deletion
of modules from the address book. Unwanted modules can now be
removed easily.

commitResults.messageTitle: Change some method headers for better code quality
Add newline to some classes to pass github CI test
commitResults.messageBody:
Modify DeleteModuleCommandTest class and DeleteTaskCommandTest
class with newline at end of file to pass github CI test.

Checkstyle errors such as unused imports and incorrect
lexicographical ordering of imports are flagged out by the build
method of gradle and are now rectified.

In order to allow users to not only edit tasks but modules as well,
the edit module functionality is implemented. This allows for
greater flexibility when a particular module was named wrongly,
and skips the steps of module deletion and then creation through
the use of a single edit step.

commitResults.messageTitle: Change isSameModuleCode method name to isSameModule
commitResults.messageBody:
Change isSameModuleCode method name in Module.java to be
isSameModule to improve consistency and readability. Files
affected by this name change were also modified. The
editCommandModule class was changed as well to better respond
to users when there is an erroneous input.

Fix checkstyle errors such as unused imports and improper
indentation.

Update Develoer Guide with the Delete Module feature as well as
the Edit Module feature.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add module name and module credit fields
commitResults.messageBody:
Modified the module class to accomodate module name and module credit
fields. Modified classes such as AddModuleCommand and
EditModuleCommand and their respective parser classes to
accomodate these new fields. The storage was also modifed via the
JsonAdaptedModule to save and process these fields, and the UI was
changed to diaplay these fields.

Remove unnecessary method in DistinctModuleList class
Change methods based on pull request comments
commitResults.messageBody:
Changed the prefix for module name in CliSyntax class to simplifiy
the input the user keys in and changed the execption thrown in the
toModelType method in JsonAdaptedModule class to reflect a more
accurate type of exception.

Modified the edit module feature by taking into account the
implications on exams and tasks tied to this
module when the module code is modified. In general, a successful
change of the module code will result in the module field of tasks
and exams to change accordingly as well.This is done to ensure
tasks and exams have a valid and existing module field.

commitResults.messageBody:
Modifications were made primarily on MainWindow.fxml,
multiple listpanels fxml files and DarkTheme.css to change the UI.
The colour scheme, each list panel portion, the input container
and result container were changed for a more aesthetic and
presentable display.

commitResults.messageBody:
Modified the edit module command and command parser class to
provide more guided messages to the user in the case of an
incorrect user input. The module code prefix and module name
prefix were also changed to more intuitive characters to improve
user friendliness.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update delete module and edit module feature
commitResults.messageBody:
The delete module feature was modified in a way such that the
deletion of a module would result in the deletion of tasks and
exams related to it. This feature is also augmented with more
guiding messages for the user, to improve user friendliness.
The command message usage is changed for both edit module
and delete module features.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update Edit Task feature with more messages
commitResults.messageBody:
Updated Edit Task feature to be more user friendly by providing
more helpful messages when user enters a wrong input. The command
message usage was also changed to be consistent with the current
command format.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update UG with delete, edit module and edit task
Amend bug for edit module feature
commitResults.messageBody:
Initially, when the edit module command is called, all exams with
the module to be edited has their module field changed to the
edited module. Also, all tasks with the module to be edited has
their module field changed to the edited module. However the
original links between these tasks and exams were not preserved.

To ensure these links are preserved, the DistinctTaskList and
DistinctExamList classes were augmented with methods to check
these links.
